<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2012/06/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>Slopwatch.Cmd</id>
    <version>0.4.0</version>
    <authors>Aaron Stannard</authors>
    <license type="expression">Apache-2.0</license>
    <licenseUrl>https://licenses.nuget.org/Apache-2.0</licenseUrl>
    <icon>logo.png</icon>
    <readme>README.md</readme>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/Aaronontheweb/dotnet-slopwatch</projectUrl>
    <description>CLI tool for detecting LLM-generated "sloppy" code patterns in .NET projects</description>
    <releaseNotes>**Bug Fixes:**
* `--config` flag now properly loads custom suppression configurations during analysis - the option was previously documented but not wired into the analysis pipeline (PR #71)
* Hook mode now falls back to full file analysis when `git status` is unavailable (e.g., outside a git repository), instead of silently returning no results (PR #71)

**Documentation:**
* Updated README examples to reflect correct `.slopwatch/config.json` schema, SW006 severity levels, and local tool installation instructions (PR #71)</releaseNotes>
    <copyright>Copyright © 2025-2026 Aaron Stannard</copyright>
